o characterize potential causal relata as patterns with specific identification criteria and noise tolerance levels, and actual causal relata as those patterns instantiated at some spatiotemporal location in the rich causal nexus as originally developed by Salmon. I develop a representation framework using phase space to precisely characterize causal relata, including their degree(s) of counterfactual robustness, causal profiles, causal connectivity, and privileged grain size. By doing so, I show how the philosophical notion of causation can be rendered in a format that is amenable for direct application of mathematical techniques from information theory such that the resulting informational measures are causal informational measures. This account provides a metaphysics of causation that supports interventionist semantics and causal modeling and discovery techniques.","topics":["metaphysics"],"si":null,"url":"https://doi.org/10.5840/jphil20171141142"},{"doi":"10.5840/jphil2017114415","title":"Feeling the Passing of Time","authors":["Giuliano Torrengo","Journal of Philosophy Inc."],"journal":"jphil","published":"2017-01-01","volume":"114","issue":"4","pages":"165-188","abstract":"","topics":["metaphysics"],"si":null,"url":"https://doi.org/10.5840/jphil2017114415"},{"doi":"10.5840/jphil201711412","title":"A Tree Can Make a Difference","authors":["Luc Lauwers","Peter Vallentyne","Journal of Philosophy Inc."],"journal":"jphil","published":"2017-01-01","volume":"114","issue":"1","pages":"33-42","abstract":"","topics":[],"si":null,"url":"https://doi.org/10.5840/jphil201711412"},{"doi":"10.5840/jphil2017114414","title":"New Books","authors":["Journal of Philosophy Inc."],"journal":"jphil","published":"2017-01-01","volume":"114","issue":"4","pages":"220-220","abstract":"","topics":[],"si":null,"url":"https://doi.org/10.5840/jphil2017114414"},{"doi":"10.5840/jphil20171141244","title":"Perception First","authors":["Lisa Miracchi","Journal of Philosophy Inc."],"journal":"jphil